s and the prospects for their peaceful resolution. Governing the World's Money surveys the frontiers of the global monetary system in ten original essays. Leading scholars of international relations and economics explore the evolution of the instruments available to policy officials for monetary governance. As they analyze the contemporary reordering of political authority in a market-oriented global economy, they open new pathways for the study of regional monetary integration and international institutional reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aInternational finance. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh1 aAndrews, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndrews, David M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCerny, Philip G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilpin, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelleiner, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenning, C. Randall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenning, C. Randall, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKahler, Miles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKenen, Peter B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcNamara, Kathleen R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOdell, John S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPadoan, Pier Carlo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPauly, Louis W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPauly, Louis W., eeditor.4edt4http://